{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TDoDmYhx97c5yhJGAaS6TU","type":"tool_result","content":"# Issue Summary: Implement todo-api Component\n\n**Issue Title:** Implement component: todo-api #1\n\n**Task ID:** `19ca7f41-ed9d-49f0-926c-5a8c136bef10`\n\n## Core Requirements\n\nBuild a RESTful backend service in Go (net/http) listening on port 9090 that manages tasks and categories using in-memory storage protected by `sync.RWMutex`.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n- Implement CRUD operations for tasks and categories\n- Enforce data integrity (validate required fields, prevent references to non-existent categories)\n- When deleting a category, set all associated task categoryIds to nil\n- Support category-based task filtering\n- Enable CORS for all origins\n- Provide `/health` endpoint\n\n## Data Models\n\n- **Category:** id, name, createdAt\n- **Task:** id, title, completed, dueDate (nullable), categoryId (nullable), createdAt, updatedAt\n\nGenerate IDs using `github.com/google/uuid` only—never accept client-supplied IDs.\n\n## Required Endpoints\n\n- Health check, category CRUD (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)\n- Task CRUD with optional categoryId filtering\n- Task completion toggle via PATCH `/tasks/{id}/complete`\n- Return appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Implement full API contract with proper error handling (400 for validation, 404 for missing resources)\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile using `golang:1.22-alpine` builder and minimal alpine final image\n- `workload.yaml` configuration file\n- Complete project structure with go.mod, handlers, and store logic"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a4126d9-69ca-4249-8836-57a0cbf0a094","uuid":"aa5a63e7-f49a-4695-ab91-362685a90c34","timestamp":"2026-04-23T10:57:49.807Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":378219,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Issue Summary: Implement todo-api Component\n\n**Issue Title:** Implement component: todo-api #1\n\n**Task ID:** `19ca7f41-ed9d-49f0-926c-5a8c136bef10`\n\n## Core Requirements\n\nBuild a RESTful backend service in Go (net/http) listening on port 9090 that manages tasks and categories using in-memory storage protected by `sync.RWMutex`.\n\n**Key Responsibilities:**\n- Implement CRUD operations for tasks and categories\n- Enforce data integrity (validate required fields, prevent references to non-existent categories)\n- When deleting a category, set all associated task categoryIds to nil\n- Support category-based task filtering\n- Enable CORS for all origins\n- Provide `/health` endpoint\n\n## Data Models\n\n- **Category:** id, name, createdAt\n- **Task:** id, title, completed, dueDate (nullable), categoryId (nullable), createdAt, updatedAt\n\nGenerate IDs using `github.com/google/uuid` only—never accept client-supplied IDs.\n\n## Required Endpoints\n\n- Health check, category CRUD (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)\n- Task CRUD with optional categoryId filtering\n- Task completion toggle via PATCH `/tasks/{id}/complete`\n- Return appropriate HTTP status codes and JSON responses\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Implement full API contract with proper error handling (400 for validation, 404 for missing resources)\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile using `golang:1.22-alpine` builder and minimal alpine final image\n- `workload.yaml` configuration file\n- Complete project structure with go.mod, handlers, and store logic","durationMs":7017,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-15201/issues/1"}}
